    "body": "`spack url stats` now also looks at packages' resources when calculating statistics.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ spack url stats\r\n==> URL stats for 3531 packages:\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\nstat                    versions        %   resources        %\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\nurl                         8335    89.3%         339    89.0%\r\n    schemes\r\n        https               6489    69.5%          93    24.4%\r\n        ftp                   32     0.3%           8     2.1%\r\n        http                1763    18.9%         237    62.2%\r\n        file                  51     0.5%           1     0.3%\r\n    checksums\r\n        md5                   26     0.3%           0     0.0%\r\n        sha256              8306    89.0%         336    88.2%\r\n        no checksum            3     0.0%           3     0.8%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\ngo                             1     0.0%           0     0.0%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\nhg                             7     0.1%           0     0.0%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\nno code                        4     0.0%           0     0.0%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\nsvn                            4     0.0%          16     4.2%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\ngit                          981    10.5%          26     6.8%\r\n    branch                   442     4.7%           4     1.0%\r\n    commit                   362     3.9%          14     3.7%\r\n    no ref                    36     0.4%           2     0.5%\r\n    tag                      141     1.5%           6     1.6%\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------\r\n```",
